---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import heroImage from '../assets/images/beader-header-3.png';
import homeImage from '../assets/images/home.png';
import manilaImage from '../assets/images/manilla.jpg';
import boyImage from '../assets/images/boy.jpg';
import storyImage from '../assets/images/lisa.png';

const anchors = [
  ['Verified Provenance', 'A named, ongoing partnership with Ercole Moretti, not a vague "inspired by Venice" claim.'],
  ['Hands-On Restoration', 'I personally restore every vintage piece, preserving its history instead of erasing it.'],
  ['Lifetime Warranty', 'Every piece is backed against defects, because I stand behind what I make.'],
  ['Real Conversations', 'Questions get answered by me, on the phone or by message - not a script.'],
];
---

<Layout
  title="The Story of Rosario"
  description="The story of Rosario Leonardi, the family name behind Rosario Leonardi Murano Glass."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="bg-[#fff]">
    <section id="hero" class="relative overflow-hidden bg-ink px-6 pb-24 pt-40 text-white sm:px-10">
      <img
        src={heroImage.src}
        alt=""
        class="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full object-cover object-center sm:object-center"
        aria-hidden="true"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-ink/70" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-[1040px] text-center">
        <div class="mb-8 flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <div class="h-px w-6 bg-gold"></div>
          <span class="font-label text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[var(--tracking-widest)] text-gold">The Story of Rosario</span>
          <div class="h-px w-6 bg-gold"></div>
        </div>
        <h1 class="mb-7 font-display text-[48px] font-light leading-none tracking-normal md:text-[78px]">
          Every Name Carries a Story.
        </h1>
        <p class="mx-auto max-w-[740px] font-sans text-[16px] font-light leading-[1.85] text-white/68">
          Long before this was a shop, Rosario Leonardi was a man and this is his story.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-[#fff]">
      <div class="grid border-b border-rule lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="relative order-2 aspect-[4/3] bg-[#fff] lg:order-1 lg:aspect-auto">
          <img src={manilaImage.src} alt="The Manila ship connected to Rosario Leonardi's crossing story" class="h-full w-full object-cover lg:absolute lg:inset-0 lg:object-left" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 flex items-center bg-[#fff] px-6 py-[7rem] sm:px-10 lg:order-2 lg:px-20">
          <div class="max-w-[620px]">
            <h2 class="mb-7 font-display text-[42px] font-light leading-none text-ink md:text-[44px]">The Crossing</h2>
            <div class="space-y-6 font-sans text-[16px] font-light leading-[1.9] text-ink-soft">
              <p>In the early 1900s, two identical twin brothers stood on a dock in Palermo, Sicily, and said goodbye to each other.</p>
              <p>One boarded a ship bound for New York. The other - Rosario - boarded a different ship, The Manilla, bound for New Orleans. Whatever words passed between them that day are lost now. What isn't lost is this: two brothers, born within minutes of each other, spent the rest of their lives an ocean and a country apart, building two entirely different futures out of the same beginning.</p>
              <p>Rosario chose Louisiana. He chose the French Quarter. And he chose to build something with his hands.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid border-b border-rule lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="flex items-center bg-[#fff] px-6 py-[7rem] sm:px-10 lg:px-20">
          <div class="ml-auto max-w-[620px]">
            <h2 class="mb-7 font-display text-[42px] font-light leading-none text-ink md:text-[44px]">A Trade Made of Fire and Iron</h2>
            <div class="space-y-6 font-sans text-[16px] font-light leading-[1.9] text-ink-soft">
              <p>In the French Quarter, Rosario became a farrier - the craftsman who shoes horses, working iron over fire until it bends into exactly what's needed. It's not a trade that forgives carelessness. You either know your material, or the horse pays for your mistake. Rosario knew his material. He became known for it, well-regarded in a city that didn't hand out reputations lightly.</p>
              <p>He met Inga Fink, a young Irish woman, and built a life with her - not in some grand house, but in half of a shotgun double at 832 Barracks Street, the kind of narrow, shared New Orleans home where you could hear your neighbors through the wall and your children through every room. Together they raised five kids in that house.</p>
              <p>No inheritance. No shortcuts. Just a trade, a marriage, and five children raised in a half of a house he earned by working iron with his own two hands.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="relative aspect-[4/3] bg-[#fff] lg:aspect-auto">
          <img src={homeImage.src} alt="The New Orleans home connected to Rosario Leonardi's story" class="h-full w-full object-cover lg:absolute lg:inset-0" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="relative order-2 aspect-[4/3] bg-[#fff] lg:order-1 lg:aspect-auto">
          <img src={boyImage.src} alt="Young boy connected to the Rosario Leonardi family story" class="h-full w-full object-cover lg:absolute lg:inset-0" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 flex items-center bg-[#fff] px-6 py-[7rem] sm:px-10 lg:order-2 lg:px-20">
          <div class="max-w-[620px]">
            <h2 class="mb-7 font-display text-[42px] font-light leading-none text-ink md:text-[44px]">What Got Passed Down</h2>
            <div class="space-y-6 font-sans text-[16px] font-light leading-[1.9] text-ink-soft">
              <p>I never met Rosario. By the time I came along, he was a name in old photographs and a few stories that survived being retold a hundred times.</p>
              <p>But something about him stuck with me anyway - maybe because of what he chose, twice. He chose New Orleans over New York, separating from the brother he shared a face with. And he chose a trade where you can't fake what you don't know. Iron tells the truth. So does horseshoeing. So, it turns out, does Murano glass.</p>
              <p>When I started this shop, I wasn't trying to build a tribute. I was trying to sell jewelry I believed in. But somewhere in sourcing real glass from real Venetian makers - refusing to pass off something fake as something true - I realized I was doing the same thing Rosario did at his forge a hundred years earlier: working with a material that doesn't lie, and refusing to cut corners on it.</p>
              <p>That's why this shop carries his name.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-ink px-6 py-24 text-white sm:px-10">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[960px] text-center">
        <h2 class="mb-7 font-display text-[42px] font-light leading-none text-white md:text-[64px]">The Through-Line</h2>
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[760px] space-y-6 font-sans text-[16px] font-light leading-[1.9] text-white/72">
          <p>Rosario crossed an ocean with nothing and built a life out of fire, iron, and honest work. I'm not shoeing horses in the French Quarter. But I'm still in the business of making sure what you're holding is real - sourced from people who actually make it, restored by hands that respect it, never dressed up as something it's not.</p>
          <p>He built it from iron. I build it from glass. Same standard.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
          <a href="/shop" class="bg-gold px-6 py-3 font-label text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[var(--tracking-wider)] text-ink transition-colors hover:bg-gold-deep hover:text-white">Shop the Collection</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="border border-white/25 px-6 py-3 font-label text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[var(--tracking-wider)] text-white transition-colors hover:border-gold hover:text-gold-light">Ask Lisa</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-[#fff] px-6 pb-0 pt-24 sm:px-10">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-[1180px] gap-14 lg:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr] lg:items-center lg:gap-24">
        <div class="pb-14 lg:pb-24">
          <h2 class="mb-8 font-display text-[45px] font-light leading-none text-ink">Real Relationships, Not Just Real Glass.</h2>
          <div class="space-y-6 font-sans text-[16px] font-light leading-[1.9] text-ink-soft">
            <p>Authentic Murano glass isn't something you stumble into. It comes from real relationships with real artisans.</p>
            <p>That's exactly why I partner directly with Ercole Moretti, one of the most exclusive bead designers in Venice. Every piece I create starts there - with glass that has a verifiable origin, not a guess.</p>
            <p>Alongside my original designs, I personally source and restore vintage Murano Millefiori pieces, bring uncirculated treasures back from my European supplier relationships, and curate freshwater pearls for those who want the same integrity in a different form.</p>
            <p>This isn't a warehouse. It's not a dropship operation. It's one person - me - making sure what reaches you is actually what I say it is.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <img src={storyImage.src} alt="Rosario Leonardi Murano glass jewelry detail" class="aspect-[4/5] w-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-ink px-6 py-24 text-white sm:px-10">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[820px] text-center">
          <div class="mb-6 flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
            <div class="h-px w-6 bg-gold"></div>
            <span class="font-label text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[var(--tracking-widest)] text-gold">Mission</span>
            <div class="h-px w-6 bg-gold"></div>
          </div>
          <h2 class="mb-7 font-display text-[42px] font-light leading-none text-white md:text-[64px]">Why I Care So Much About "Real."</h2>
          <div class="mx-auto max-w-[760px] space-y-6 font-sans text-[16px] font-light leading-[1.9] text-white/70">
            <p>The online market for Murano glass is flooded with mass-produced imports and vague sourcing claims. I've seen too many people get burned - paying real money for something that isn't what it claims to be.</p>
            <p>I'd rather be the seller who proves it, every time, than the seller who just says "trust me."</p>
          </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-[#fff] px-6 py-24 sm:px-10">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1180px] text-center">
        <h3 class="mb-10 font-display text-[34px] font-light leading-tight text-ink md:text-[44px]">What Makes This Different</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-px border border-rule bg-rule text-left md:grid-cols-2">
          {anchors.map(([title, body]) => (
            <article class="bg-[#fff] p-8">
              <h4 class="mb-4 font-display text-[28px] font-normal leading-tight text-ink">{title}</h4>
              <p class="font-sans text-[14px] font-light leading-[1.85] text-ink-soft">{body}</p>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-ink px-6 py-24 text-white sm:px-10">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[960px] text-center">
        <h2 class="mb-7 font-display text-[42px] font-light leading-none md:text-[64px]">Collecting, Gifting, or Creating</h2>
        <p class="mx-auto mb-8 max-w-[760px] font-sans text-[16px] font-light leading-[1.9] text-white/70">
          I built this shop for the people who care about getting it right: collectors who want provenance, families looking for a gift that actually means something, and makers who need materials they can trust. Whoever you are, I'd love to help you find the piece that's actually yours.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
          <a href="/shop" class="bg-gold px-6 py-3 font-label text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[var(--tracking-wider)] text-ink transition-colors hover:bg-gold-deep hover:text-white">Shop the Collection</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="border border-white/25 px-6 py-3 font-label text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[var(--tracking-wider)] text-white transition-colors hover:border-gold hover:text-gold-light">Get in Touch</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
